We have our first cosplay guest announcement! We are beyond honored to welcome @_sammills and their itasha @windhashiira to MoTownCon! They will be one of our cosplay judges for this year so bring your A Game! 

Sam is a NJ based cosplayer who has been creating costumes since 2011. They’re best known for their Demon Slayer cosplays and specialize in prop building, sfx makeup, and photo editing. When not working on cosplay, they enjoy baking and working on their Sanemi Itasha.

Check out their amazing cosplays and be sure to stop by their booth at MoTownCon!

Not @animenyc being a week out and me now questioning my lineup. SOS send help.
.
I’m debating between all these tbh, Choso will definitely be happening at some point, just don’t know if I want to wear him for a whole day or not. Would love to bring Zohakuten, but wearing him through the NYC wind tunnels and taking on NJ transit sounds like a whole process lmao. Muzan would have some upgrades (and I can actually get more content), and it’s just fun to wear Gun Fiend, Bakugou, and Ghost.
I should be bringing another clone and Kaiser from Blue Lock though, so just need to pick one or two.
.
Indecisiveness aside I’m hype, it’s my 6th year and I’m stoked to be an official influencer for one of my fave cons. Hope to see y’all there.
.
